Mother of kidnapped journalist Shiraaz Mohamed is at Chiawelo voting station where President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to vote today. She is there so she can ask the president to help bring her son back home after he was kidnapped in Syria. The Department of International Relations and Co-operations (Dirco) has been mum on the issue of the kidnapped journalist.A video emerged showing Mohamed pleading for the South African government to assist in securing his freedom, is proof that the journalist is alive. His kidnappers want $1.5 million for his release.